history.content: Given the classes you have already taken (and the fact that you are even thinking about taking EE 227B), you should have a mathematical maturity that is well beyond what is required for CS 70. So for you, CS 70 should be a fairly easy class. I would say then that the only real classes you are taking are CS 61C + EE 123/227B. Two techs are doable.

(I have taken EE 127, 54, 16A / 16B).

Which EE course should I take (to not get overwhelmed)?

Or should I just forego the last EE course altogether?

Thanks
